text: Máté Fenyvesi (20 September 1933 – 17 February 2022) was a Hungarian footballer and politician.Meghalt a Ferencváros VVK-győztes, Európa-bajnoki bronzérmes labdarúgója He played for the national team from 1954 until 1966, making 76 appearances. A politician, he was a member of the National Assembly from 1990 until 1992 and again from 1998 until 2006. Fenyvesi died on 17 February 2022, at the age of 88. ==References== Category:1933 births Category:2022 deaths Category:Hungarian footballers Category:Hungarian politicians
title: Máté Fenyvesi
